Aquí los libros hablan por ti: Here the books speak for you
Eñe 2024: 150 voces y 90 actos en el gra: Eñe 2024: 150 voices and 90 acts at the great creation festival in Madrid
La capital acogerá entre el 9 y el 26 de: The Festival will have its main stage at the Círculo de Bellas Artes in Madrid, as always, but it will spread throughout Madrid and will have an extension in Malaga (until December 1st)
Eñe celebrará actos en el Ateneo de Madr: Eñe will hold events at the Ateneo de Madrid (a performance called Me Acuerdo , in the style of George Perec), the Museo del Prado (Miquel Barceló and Borja Hermoso will talk in front of Las Meninas) , at the Regional Library of Madrid (there will be a day dedicated to fantastic and transmedia narrative) at the Real Academia Española, at the Instituto Cervantes, at the Serrería Belga, in Alcalá de Henares and Chinchón...
Un momento especial en el programa es el: A special moment in the programme is promised by the intervention of the Princess of Asturias Award for Literature, Ana Blandiana , who will read the verses of the Russian Anna Akhmatova at the Teatro de la Abadía and will speak of her life as a yearning for democracy. On that same stage, the Chilean poet Raúl Zurita will be accompanied by his Spanish colleagues Antonio Lucas and Aurora Luque, both winners of the Loewe International Poetry Prize. Eñe will also have a space for the co-official languages ​​of the State with windows to Basque literature, curated by the writer Katixa Aguirre ; Catalan literature, curated by the actors and playwrights Nao Albet and Marcel Borrás ; and, for the first time, to Galician literature, curated by the writer Xesús Fraga .
